header.gameNote: PARADISE JAM AT ST JOHN VIRGIN ISLANDS

article.headline: Old Dominion 74, Georgia 65
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Valdas Vasylius scored 19 points to lead Old Dominion to a 74-65 victory over Georgia at the Paradise Jam tournament on Friday night. Brandon Johnson and Drew Williamson each scored 12 points for Old Dominion, which faces Fordham on Saturday. Sundiara Gaines had 15 points and Levi Stukes and Terrance Woodbury each scored 14 for Georgia, which takes on Fordham on Sunday, in the six-team round-robin tournament. The teams traded scoring runs in the second half. Old Dominion had a 20-0 outburst, capped by a sweeping underhand field goal by Drew Williamson that gave the Monarchs a 55-39 lead with less than 8 minutes left. The Bulldogs rallied within two points with 3:47 left. Stukes hit two 3-pointers late in the game, but Vasylius sealed the win with a dunk with 8 seconds left.
